<paragraph id="099995002D770D900F45FC580675189E" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">West Indies (Dominica, Jamaica, Montserrat, Puerto Rico, St. Lucia, Virgin Islands).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B498C61F02ACC4B51EC7D065387B26E6" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="77C0AB5452E5B8B0B3663323CA14BDB6" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F2C1BB2BD458858C1060745B98A8B5E3" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
This species is widespread in the West Indies, being described using material from Jamaica, Puerto Rico, and the Virgin Islands (Van Duzee 1927) and later reported from Dominica (
<bibRefCitation id="BBEE30F260F7952B532C3CDBB8A8EAD7" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.185" author="Robinson, H" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 141" refId="B67" refString="Robinson, H, 1975. Bredin-Archbold-Smithsonian Biological Survey of Dominica, the family Dolichopodidae with some related Antillean and Panamanian species (Diptera). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 185: 1 - 141, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.185" title="Bredin-Archbold-Smithsonian Biological Survey of Dominica, the family Dolichopodidae with some related Antillean and Panamanian species (Diptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.185" volume="185" year="1975">Robinson 1975</bibRefCitation>
) and St. Lucia (
<bibRefCitation id="6C0920C9B4C0F5A59B0AAD67A602433D" author="Bickel, DJ" journalOrPublisher="Studia dipterologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="545 - 560" refId="B7" refString="Bickel, DJ, 2002. New synonyms in the Nearctic and Neotropical Sciapodinae (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Studia dipterologica 9: 545 - 560" title="New synonyms in the Nearctic and Neotropical Sciapodinae (Diptera: Dolichopodidae)." volume="9" year="2002">Bickel 2002</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="42962EC45B74C41C3F5FAE08FBD444B1" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.185" author="Robinson, H" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 141" refId="B67" refString="Robinson, H, 1975. Bredin-Archbold-Smithsonian Biological Survey of Dominica, the family Dolichopodidae with some related Antillean and Panamanian species (Diptera). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 185: 1 - 141, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.185" title="Bredin-Archbold-Smithsonian Biological Survey of Dominica, the family Dolichopodidae with some related Antillean and Panamanian species (Diptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.185" volume="185" year="1975">Robinson (1975)</bibRefCitation>
described this species as 
<taxonomicName id="DE7BFC1B59A0FB8A95A22213EA85B927" authorityName="Robinson" authorityYear="1975" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Condylostylus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Condylostylus perpilosus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perpilosus">
<emphasis id="B4626B8A90F8CD6D71DA6CC746A0318B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Condylostylus perpilosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="9A5D4BB602AC8F30FB20130EEACB5BBE" genus="C." lsidName="C. albiciliatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="albiciliatus">
<emphasis id="C9B259278D683AF0A9F5E6DDD26C4C99" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">C. albiciliatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="6697EF1C144A59C42F44D4A860CA5646" author="Bickel, DJ" journalOrPublisher="Studia dipterologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="545 - 560" refId="B7" refString="Bickel, DJ, 2002. New synonyms in the Nearctic and Neotropical Sciapodinae (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Studia dipterologica 9: 545 - 560" title="New synonyms in the Nearctic and Neotropical Sciapodinae (Diptera: Dolichopodidae)." volume="9" year="2002">Bickel (2002)</bibRefCitation>
. Adults of 
<taxonomicName id="E5DA40DF5C3F8DC01C36FC09D129A4D2" genus="C." lsidName="C. albiciliatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="albiciliatus">
<emphasis id="16FB1D3EE307B297F464F5057AE0831F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">C. albiciliatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appear to be active year-round on Montserrat.
</paragraph>
